 13→+## Unattended Execution
 14→+
 15→+Today, Nurge supports unattended local execution through a generated wrapper around the dispatcher:
 16→+
 17→+```bash
 18→+nurge dispatcher install
 19→+```
 20→+
 21→+That command writes:
 22→+
 23→+- `.nurge/bin/dispatcher-run.sh` — runs `nurge dispatcher run --execute --sync-replies`
 24→+- `.nurge/automation/dispatcher.plist` — macOS `launchd` agent template
 25→+- `.nurge/logs/dispatcher.log` — combined scheduler output
 26→+
 27→+Use the printed cron line or copy the plist into `~/Library/LaunchAgents` on macOS. This works with the terminal closed, but the machine still needs to stay on and authenticated.
 28→+
 29→+Convex + Unipile remains the later path for true remote execution when the user's machine is off.
 30→+
 31→ ## Learns From Every Conversation
 32→ 
 33→ Nurge gets smarter the more you use it. Every Claude Code session — tone feedback, rejected drafts, ICP refinements — is captured and stored locally. Skills automatically improve over time without you doing anything.
